headline: Jensen Huang Just Delivered a Startling Message About Nvidia's Future in China
summary: The Nvidia CEO spoke about the company’s future in China during the company’s recent earnings report.  To use an old saying, the world was Nvidia's (NASDAQ: NVDA) oyster.  The Biden administration in 2022 launched export controls, limiting the types of AI chips that could be sold to the major market of China, then earlier this year issued the AI Diffusion Rule to further strengthen that position.

headline: Can AMD Stock Turn a $25,000 Investment Into $1 Million by the Time You Retire?
summary: The artificial-intelligence chip market is growing at a feverish pace.  Advanced Micro Devices (NASDAQ: AMD), the popular chipmaker more commonly referred to as AMD, has been off to a sluggish start to 2025.  The launch of new AI chips last year and some improved results could give investors reason to be more optimistic about the potential for the stock to deliver some mammoth returns.
